vehicle.parts

Class PartsSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<E>
        • java.util.HashSet<Part>
          • vehicle.parts.PartsSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<Part>, java.util.Collection<Part>, java.util.Set<Part>

    public class PartsSet
extends java.util.HashSet<Part>
    Represents a this of parts. In this set it is impossible to add two different parts of the same type. This set does not permit the null element.
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • PartsSet

        public PartsSet()
        Creates a new, empty partsSet

      • PartsSet

        public PartsSet(java.util.Collection<Part> collection)
        Creates a new partsSet containing the elements of the given collection. If the collection contains multiple parts of the same type, one of these parts will be randomly selected and the other parts will not be contained by this set.

      • PartsSet

        public PartsSet(Part[] array)
        Creates a new partsSet containing the elements of the given array. If the array contains multiple parts of the same type, one of these parts will be randomly selected and the other parts will not be contained by this set.
